tldr, this basically allows for:

```js
export default {
  async fetch(request: Request): Promise<Response> {
    console.log('Request URL:', request.url); // https://localhost:4321
    const state = new FetchState(request);
    return await astro(state);
  },
} satisfies Fetchable;
```

## Changes

- Moves X-Forwarded-Proto/Host/Port resolution into `FetchState`'s constructor, so headers set by user code in `src/app.ts` before creating `FetchState` are reflected in `Astro.url` and `Astro.clientAddress`. Previously these headers were resolved before the Fetchable handler's `fetch()` was called...
